---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Self-hosted docs"
  description="Run the Thumbrella standalone binary locally or in your own infrastructure."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="self hosted"
    title="Run the standalone Rust binary"
    lede="Use the self-hosted binary when you want a totally free setup that works online, offline, or fully disconnected."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Download the latest release binary for your platform.</li>
      <li>Use the CLI for direct thumbnail generation.</li>
      <li>Run the built-in server when you want a local or private HTTP endpoint.</li>
    </ol>
    <pre><code>{`thumbrella thumb ./sample.mov --at 12s --output ./sample.webp
thumbrella serve --port 8000`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      This mode is a strong fit for desktop applications, CI jobs, internal tools, and air-gapped
      environments where external service dependencies are a non-starter.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>